Phlegmatic\n calm and quiet. For them, first of all, calmness and a positive emotional background in the team, among friends or in the family are important. Such people are excellent at handling large amounts of information, as well as the task of classifying and distributing them. They often act as intermediaries in conflicts. They are not used to showing their emotions and feelings, but at the same time they try to delve as deeply as possible into the essence of other people. On the other hand, phlegmatics are often selfish, easily judge others, resist change, and try to participate little in any activities. A phlegmatic person can be described as an "observer"

Melancholic and thoughtful. Such people approach the solution of problems thoroughly and very carefully. Therefore, they are able to find answers to those questions that would confuse others. Melancholics are by nature deeply feeling and thinking natures, who often see the negative aspects of life rather than the positive ones. They are self-reliant, independent, and fully committed to what they do. Very often they are perfectionists – they set themselves such heights that are extremely difficult to achieve. These are people who are capable of truly deep love and devotion. Melancholics are more likely to suffer from depression and apathy. A melancholic can be described as a "thinker"

Choleric\pambitic and power-seeking. They are leaders by nature: they always strive for control, always try to do everything perfectly. They are focused primarily on their goals. Weakly sensitive to the emotions and experiences of other people. For them, it is important that the job is done, and done perfectly. Such people are impulsive and active. Irritability and intemperance-this is about them. Relying on logic, analytics, their own opinion and their own position are their resources. But along with these qualities, such people have the greatest difficulties with controlling their anger and lack of patience. They always want facts first, not emotions. A choleric person can be described as a "doer"

Sanguine\nThe tireless seeker, doer, and restless. Sanguine people are the soul of the company. They always try to be the center of attention, to amuse others and to have fun themselves. The most hated thing for them is monotonous and routine work. This they try to avoid at all costs. They are cheerful, fervent, always on the move and searching. But even these optimists have their drawbacks: they do not always finish the job they started. Sanguine people are more likely to become victims of various types of addiction: tobacco, alcohol, drugs, gambling. They\'re also often late for anything. A sanguine person can be described as a "speaker"
